Line Follower Robot 🤖

📌 Description

This project is an autonomous robot that follows a predefined path (usually a black line on a white surface) using IR sensors. The robot continuously detects the path and adjusts its movement accordingly.

🎯 Objective

To design and implement a robot capable of path tracking using sensor-based feedback and control logic.

🔧 Components Used

- Arduino Uno
- IR Sensors (2 or more)
- L298N Motor Driver
- DC Motors with wheels
- Chassis
- Battery pack

⚙️ Working Principle

The IR sensors detect the contrast between the black line and the white surface. Based on sensor inputs:

- If the robot is on track → moves forward
- If it deviates → adjusts left or right
  The Arduino processes these inputs and controls motor direction using the motor driver.

🚀 Features

- Autonomous navigation
- Real-time path correction
- Simple and efficient design

